&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with senior leadership across Samsara (Sales, Finance, Operations, Accounting, Legal, and Product) to influence deal outcomes and achieve corporate financial goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute at a high pace and ensure continuous improvement through business insights and cross-functional influence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a fulfilling and inclusive work experience by hiring, managing and developing a high-performing team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, your impact will be highly visible and contribute directly to Samsara’s business performance and success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a remote position open to candidates residing in the US &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;except&lt;/span&gt; the San Francisco Bay Metro Area, NYC Metro Area, and Washington, D.C. Metro Area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direct support to Sales and Sales leadership to help shape complex Enterprise transactions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales and Finance leadership to inform and execute a syndicated deal strategy, including pricing, payment structures, commercial terms, legal and product considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize data and real-time reporting to support decision-making/executive communication and to identify areas of improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate operational excellence to provide a delightful Sales and Customer experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong cross-functional partnerships, proactively communicate and iterate on feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion, role model, and embed Samsara’s cultural principles (Focus on Customer Success, Build for the Long Term, Adopt a Growth Mindset, Be Inclusive, Win as a Team) as we scale globally and across new offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, develop and lead an inclusive, engaged, and high-performing team of deal managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements for the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of combined experience in Deal Desk, Finance, Sales, Sales Operations, Revenue Operations or equivalent roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in complex deal negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial acumen, ability to translate corporate financial goals into deal support strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to hire, manage, and develop talent and lead a high-performing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with senior management and Enterprise Customers, distill key concepts, and influence business choices&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to synthesize data into actionable insights, make data-driven conclusions and establish recurring reporting to monitor performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CRM, CPQ and CLM tools and familiarity with downstream systems (eg, ERP, reporting visualizations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An ideal candidate also has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing a Deal Desk or Commercial Incubation team within a high-growth SaaS business at scale ($1 billion + ARR)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Salesforce and NetSuite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samsara’s Compensation Philosophy: &lt;/strong&gt;Samsara’s compensation program is designed to deliver Total Direct Compensation (based on role, level, and geography) that is at or above market. We do this through our base salary + bonus/variable + restricted stock unit awards (RSUs) for eligible roles. For eligible roles, a new hire RSU award may be awarded at the time of hire, and additional RSU refresh grants may be awarded annually.&lt;/p&gt;
